full_text:
Think the difference in styles is what sets the two apart, and I take development, twists, and climax to Breaking Bad over the ideas and themes hashed out in the Sopranos

Each feature for both are great, and not to say the dialogue in BB and suspense in Sopranos aren‚Äôt also A+

full_text:
Where it almost feels like a decision was made to wrap up the Sopranos, Breaking Bad unfolds and is completed flawlessly, all while delivering edge of the seat, jaw dropping moments every single season

I think of Breaking Bad to be similarly written as Coen Brother tales
